Friends and family:



A quick note: I've spent the last year or so creating a documentary about
the terrible secular education some kids get in ultra-Orthodox yeshivas in
Brooklyn and upstate New York. People who saw some things in the Jewish
media last week have asked how they can watch it.



Here's the 90 second trailer:

https://vimeo.com/joekolman/trailer



And here's the link to watch the entire 40-minute rough cut, which is
available until Tuesday at 5PM.

https://watch.showandtell.film/watch/anunorthodoxeducation-facebook



And here are a couple articles that appeared recently in the Jerusalem Post
and the Jewish Daily Forward.



https://www.jpost.com/diaspora/new-documentary-tackles-secular-education-debate-in-new-york-city-yeshivas-675773



https://forward.com/opinion/473301/some-feel-trapped-in-ultra-orthodoxy-why-dont-we-help-when-they-try-to/



If you feel so inclined, you can even donate to the film, as I've found
raising money for independent documentaries is even harder than pitching
exotic fixed-income securities.



For those who haven't heard from me in a while, I'm always happy to
reconnect and here what you're up to.


My next email blast is scheduled for 2026.



Joe

